	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">I'm farming Matar ;)</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sun, Sep 30th 10:17 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [2.14]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I couldn't help it, i've just hit 34 as a ranger, and omw to Permafrost to bully the icegoblins,&nbsp;&nbsp;chanced upon Matar icebear.<br/><br/>Snare, Stingingswarm, Bow kite for a while engage in melee, and he started to run at 20% life.<br/><br/>Looted a cloak of him, and then hit track, hmm? he was up again. I ran over, medded near him, and this 34 warrior asks if he cna share the spawn. I say sure, no prob. I ask him if he needs help with Matar and got a curt reply "Don't need help from a ranger! i'm a warrior." ok fine. so while waiting, for him to heal up to full i just cast 4 light heals on him to heal him to full and 1 skin like rock to buff him for the fight. Then i sit back down to med, and on hindsight i hit the AFK button. Less than a minute later i get tells from this warrior, saying "elph me plz". Feeling evil, i decide to let him rot, since "he doesn't need help from a ranger".<br/><br/>Of course he gets the "AFK" reply from me.<br/><br/>Then here's what got my goat, i hear footsteps running past my medding point(underneath the stone giant statue), i thought it sounded like a Snow leopard, then suddenly <br/>=CRUNCH!!=<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear hits YOU for 71 points of damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was hit for 2 points of melee damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was pierced by thorns.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear hits YOU for 71 points of damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was hit for 2 points of melee damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was pierced by thorns.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear bashes YOU for 18 points of damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was hit for 2 points of melee damage.<br/>&gt;Matar Icebear was pierced by thorns.<br/>&gt;You are stunned!<br/><br/>I was like WTF? Half a bub of health down for no reason. Since i was SoWed i decide to stand up and make a break for it first and assess the situation. I see a Matar Icebear at abt 50%life, and an injured warrior at less that 20%(less than 1 bub) who trained me and kept running. <br/><br/>Needless to say, i was very pissed off. I sent a reply to him;<br/>RNG: Why did you train him to me? I was AFK and medding!<br/>WAR: I didnt see you.help me plz<br/>RNG: Of course i'll help you, i have you on track, better keep running.<br/>WAR: ? i am running.<br/><br/>Then while tracking him, i proceed to lead Matar all the way back to that aggrogant POS warrior. The warrior, being low on health, cannot run very far and has to fight anyway.<br/><br/>WAR: help me snare him plz heal me plz thks<br/><br/>Feeling pretty frustrated, i decide to use him as my personal pet. I cast a skin like rock on him (heals him since it was already active from previous cast), then i cast Shield of thistles on him.<br/><br/>Of course, Matar proceeds to slay him and then i slay Matar, who thanks to my live damage shield, fights me at less than 40% life, and he starts to run even before doing more than 200damage to me.<br/><br/>Rule of the day: Be nice, and people might just help ya out.<br/><br/>By the way i'm farming Matar, since his cloaks are not lore, and i collected like 8 before i went to Gfay to sell them all at 200pp obo, but 4 were bargained down to 150pp and 1 was bargained down to 120pp plus a bronze cloak.<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
